Sentencas: Modified by Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-delta(SDC) nanoparticles (NPs), SmBaCo2O5+delta(SBCO) double perovskite oxide is evaluated as a promising cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: A SmBaCo2O5+&DELTA double perovskite with epitaxially grown Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-δ nanoparticles as a promising cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SDC NPs are epitaxially grown on the surface of SBCO with (220) planes of SDC aligning smoothly to (020) or (100) planes of SBCO, forming a tight, coherent connection at the interface.
Titulo: A SmBaCo2O5+&DELTA double perovskite with epitaxially grown Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-δ nanoparticles as a promising cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The influence of this modification on thermal expansion, oxygen diffusion, electrical conductivity and electrochemical properties is investigated thoroughly in this work.
Titulo: A SmBaCo2O5+&DELTA double perovskite with epitaxially grown Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-δ nanoparticles as a promising cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The designed SBCO-SDC cathode material demonstrates a lower thermal expansion coefficient (TEC), similar to 16.4 x 10(-6)K(-1), than that of the unmodified SBCO, similar to 20.9 x 10(-6)K(-1).
Titulo: A SmBaCo2O5+&DELTA double perovskite with epitaxially grown Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-δ nanoparticles as a promising cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: While SDC coating results in a decreased total electrical conductivity, it facilitates oxygen bulk diffusion and improves the surface exchange reaction kinetics.
Titulo: A SmBaCo2O5+&DELTA double perovskite with epitaxially grown Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-δ nanoparticles as a promising cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Coating with SDC NPs can accelerate the rate-determining process of dissociation of the absorbed molecular oxygen, especially at intermediate temperatures.
Titulo: A SmBaCo2O5+&DELTA double perovskite with epitaxially grown Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-δ nanoparticles as a promising cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Accordingly, the constructed symmetrical cell with the La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta(LSGM) electrolyte shows lower polarization resistance values, if the SBCO-SDC cathode is utilized.
Titulo: A SmBaCo2O5+&DELTA double perovskite with epitaxially grown Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-δ nanoparticles as a promising cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Also, the LSGM electrolyte-supported (300 mu m) full cell is found to deliver a high power density of 800 mW cm(-2)at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: A SmBaCo2O5+&DELTA double perovskite with epitaxially grown Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-δ nanoparticles as a promising cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Owing to the strong and coherent interfacial connection, the developed cathode demonstrates a relatively steady electrochemical performance.
Titulo: A SmBaCo2O5+&DELTA double perovskite with epitaxially grown Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-δ nanoparticles as a promising cathode for solid oxide fuel cells
